# xpc_uint64_create(_:)

**Function**

Creates an XPC unsigned integer object.

## Declaration

```swift
func xpc_uint64_create(_ value: UInt64) -> xpc_object_t
```

## Parameters

- **value**: The unsigned integer value which is to be boxed.

## Return Value

A new unsigned integer object.

## Number objects

- **xpc_double_create(_:)**: Creates an XPC double object.
- **xpc_double_get_value(_:)**: Returns the underlying double-precision floating point value from an object.
- **xpc_int64_create(_:)**: Creates an XPC signed integer object.
- **xpc_int64_get_value(_:)**: Returns the underlying signed 64-bit integer value from an object.
- **xpc_uint64_get_value(_:)**: Returns the underlying unsigned 64-bit integer value from an object.
